{
  "texts": [
    "DeepLabv3 DeepLabv3 was an improvement made over DeepLabv2, in this version the problem of segmenting objects at multiple scale was solved by designing and employing atrous in cascade to capture multiscale context by adopting multiple atrous rates. 3.",
    "DeepLabv3+ Deeplabv3+ is an improvement over DeepLabv3+.",
    "In this version semantic labels are assigned to every pixel in the given input image.",
    "RetinaNetRetinaNet is used for one stage object detection models.RetinaNet provides good results in dense and small objects detection.",
    "RetinaNet is mostly used with aerial and satellite object imagery."
  ]
}